    • Method Detail

      • getColumnId

        public final String getColumnId(int columnIndex)
        Returns the identifier of a given column specified by the column index in the underlying table. For data tables that are retrieved by queries, the column identifier is set by the data source, and can be used to refer to columns when using the query language.
        Parameters:
        columnIndex - the column position
        Returns:
        the identifier of the given column index

      • getColumnLabel

        public final String getColumnLabel(int columnIndex)
        Returns the label of a given column specified by the column index in the underlying table. The column label is typically displayed as part of the visualization. For example the column label can be displayed as a column header in a table, or as the legend label in a pie chart. For data tables that are retrieved by queries, the column label is set by the data source, or by the label clause of the query language.
        Parameters:
        columnIndex - the column position
        Returns:
        the label of the given column index

      • getColumnPattern

        public final String getColumnPattern(int columnIndex)
        Returns the formatting pattern used to format the values of the specified column. columnIndex should be a number greater than or equal to zero, and less than the number of columns as returned by the getNumberOfColumns() method. For data tables that are retrieved by queries, The column pattern is set by the data source, or by the format clause of the query language. An example of a pattern is '#,##0.00'. For more on patterns see the query language reference.
        Parameters:
        columnIndex - the column position
        Returns:
        the pattern of the given column index

      • getColumnProperties

        public final Properties getColumnProperties(int columnIndex)
        Returns a map of all properties for the specified column. Note that the properties object is returned by reference, so changing values in the retrieved object changes them in the DataTable. columnIndex is the numeric index of the column to retrieve properties for.
        Parameters:
        columnIndex - the column position
        Returns:
        the properties of the given column index

      • getColumnPropertyBoolean

        public final boolean getColumnPropertyBoolean(int columnIndex,
                               String propertyName)
        Returns the value of a named property, or null if no such property is set for the specified column. The return type varies, depending on the property. columnIndex should be a number greater than or equal to zero, and less than the number of columns as returned by the getNumberOfColumns() method. name is the property name, as a string.
        Parameters:
        columnIndex - the column position
        propertyName - a property name
        Returns:
        the property value of the given column and property name

      • getColumnRange

        public final ColumnRange getColumnRange(int columnIndex)
        Returns the minimal and maximal values of values in a specified column. The returned object has properties min and max. If the range has no values, min and max will contain null. columnIndex should be a number greater than or equal to zero, and less than the number of columns as returned by the getNumberOfColumns() method.
        Parameters:
        columnIndex - the column position
        Returns:
        an object with minimal and maximal values of values in the specified column

      • getFilteredRows

        public final com.google.gwt.core.client.JsArrayNumber getFilteredRows(com.google.gwt.core.client.JsArray<RowFilter> filters)
        Returns the row indexes for rows that match all of the given filters. The indexes are returned in ascending order. The output of this method can be used as input to DataView.setRows() to change the displayed set of rows in a visualization.
        Parameters:
        filters - An array of objects that describe an acceptable cell value.
        Returns:
        the row indexes for rows that match all of the given filters.
